00:30:07,160 --> 00:30:09,760
 I think that's really critical, right?

541
00:30:09,760 --> 00:30:12,480
 Because I could not on my own have accomplished those things.

542
00:30:12,480 --> 00:30:15,760
 I had no shot at doing any of that.

543
00:30:15,760 --> 00:30:20,920
 But because the Lord was building, those things were able to be accomplished.

544
00:30:20,920 --> 00:30:24,240
 Ask yourself, is this something God is building or something I'm building on my own?

545
00:30:24,240 --> 00:30:30,580
 Because if God is building it, hear this, it will not fail.

546
00:30:30,580 --> 00:30:33,960
 At the same time, it'll probably be hard.

547
00:30:33,960 --> 00:30:36,800
 Like let's not live in a Christian fairy tale where it's like, "God's doing it.

548
00:30:36,800 --> 00:30:40,280
 Therefore, I will have no problems and butterflies and rainbows everywhere."

549
00:30:40,280 --> 00:30:42,560
 That's not our reality.

550
00:30:42,560 --> 00:30:44,520
 See God grows us in that tension.

551
00:30:44,520 --> 00:30:48,760
 God anchors our faith through those difficulties, but he comes through.

552
00:30:48,760 --> 00:30:53,280
 He doesn't start what he's not going to finish.

553
00:30:53,280 --> 00:30:56,840
 That's not our God.

