00:32:47,360 --> 00:32:51,200
 the person who applies or who provides for ourselves.

579
00:32:51,200 --> 00:32:56,080
 Perhaps there's a day where we physically rest, where we mentally rest, where we bring

580
00:32:56,080 --> 00:33:01,880
 our anxieties and our cares to God, where we remember who he is.

581
00:33:01,880 --> 00:33:07,480
 See in the Old Testament, when God's people would rest, God would, he would provide for

582
00:33:07,480 --> 00:33:08,480
 them.

583
00:33:08,480 --> 00:33:09,480
 It's interesting.

584
00:33:09,480 --> 00:33:13,700
 It requires you to rest before you get that provision, but he will provide.

585
00:33:13,700 --> 00:33:19,920
 Do we have faith enough to take a day, a week, and dedicate it just to remembering that we

586
00:33:19,920 --> 00:33:24,680
 are ever dependent on him?

